dataObject.content: Trump signed a GOP tax bill in 2017 that cut taxes for the middle class but delivered a larger tax break for the wealthiest Americans.

annotationData.content: {"category":{"label":"Biased"},"rationale":"He wouldn't raise taxes by a penny on anyone making less than $400,000. In contrast, Congressional Republicans would continue the big handouts"}
